A man who damaged a Labour politicians' office has been sentenced to 300 hours of unpaid work. Joshua Morris, 31, admitted criminal damage at the office of Llanelli MP Dame Nia Griffith and MS Lee Waters.Morris, from Heol Gwili, Llanelli, damaged the building in Pottery Street on 1 October. He pleaded guilty at the town's magistrates' court on Friday.
Dyfed-Powys Police said there was window damage and scorch marks to the front of the building. Dame Nia is shadow minister for international trade and the cabinet office. Mr Waters is deputy minister for climate change in the Welsh government.Morris was also been ordered to pay costs and a victim surcharge totalling Â£614.
